<br>
First save your rear styles for the mez.  Always hit 1 attack unstyled on casters just to break MT, THEN mez.  Then get off the rear style, the caster will turn to root/stun, hit your 2nd rear style and step through him.<br>
<br>
Remember once you land the opening shot havor/or arctic you don't have to KEEP standing in the front of rear of the guy, it will still land.<br>
<br>
Remember in 8v8 or big fights if you rush in, your job is taking out casters.   Toss that first mez quick on first robe/healer you see, then get on a second.   On the second, Immediately use your snare that will interupt him, and close to melee, 2 shouts and style.    Remember you got 20 secs and you haven't mezd this guy yet, so if he's running (which 99% of the time he'll take off running) you pop the mez on him again.  Then rear style again.<br>
<br>
8v8 when you hit the other group, never stop, mez run through them and come back around looken for your target.<br>
<br>
If you have some specific scenario's I'll try to give ya some more tips. <p>&lt;center&gt;<br>
